USER: if there is a agent.md file in the same location as where the .coden file is loaded will this tool load and refrence that instruction as well?  so if we have many .coden files in a folder with a central agent.md file they will all share it?

ASSISTANT:
Not reliably, as currently written.

`coden.mjs` does not explicitly read `agent.md`/`AGENTS.md`; it builds prompts from the `.coden` sections (`Instructions`, `Pinned`, `Summary`, `Conversation`) only.

Because you run `codex exec` with `--cd` set to the topic folder, Codex CLI might apply `AGENTS.md` implicitly if the CLI supports that behavior, but your wrapper is not guaranteeing it.

If you want guaranteed shared folder-level instructions across many `.coden` files, I should add explicit loading of `AGENTS.md` (or `agent.md`) from the topic folder and merge it into every turn’s prompt.

