USER: if I created the repo with no branches and have this none attached folder how do I connect it to the repo and start pushing to it

ASSISTANT:
In `C:\Mine\Coden`, run these commands in PowerShell.

If this folder is **not** a git repo yet:

```powershell
cd C:\Mine\Coden
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin <YOUR_REPO_URL>
git push -u origin main
```

If this folder is **already** a git repo (but no remote attached):

```powershell
cd C:\Mine\Coden
git remote add origin <YOUR_REPO_URL>
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

Useful checks:

```powershell
git status
git remote -v
git branch
```

If `origin` already exists and is wrong, fix it with:

```powershell
git remote set-url origin <YOUR_REPO_URL>
```

